whois.ac.za._Notes: I could not figure out how to get a meaningful response from whois.ac.za:43.

whois.alt.za._Notes: No new registrations for .alt.za are allowed according to http://www.internet.org.za/slds.html .

_Notes: This server supports the wild card character '%', but it may not appear within the first three characters.  Websocket Whois does not take advantage of this; since the TLD is for such a limited use it did not seem worthwhile to write special code just for it.

whois.cctld.uz.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^sorry, but domain: "(\S+)", not found in database$

_Notes: Unreliable.  Sometimes says 'Queried interval is too short'.  Maybe I should space out all queries to this server by one second.

whois.co.ug._Notes: The server whois.co.ug:43 was malfunctioning the last time we checked.

_Notes: Sometimes takes 5-10 seconds to respond to queries.  TODO: ignore this server?

whois.domain-registry.nl._RateLimitNote: It said: only 1 request per second allowed, try again later

whois.domain.kg.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^data not found\. this domain is available for registration\.$

whois.domainregistry.my.RateLimitNote: It said: Please note that the query limit is 500 per day from the same IP.

whois.dot.tk.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^invalid query or domain name not known in dot tk domain registry$

whois.edu.cn._Notes: Server seems to be down or has moved.

whois.net.za._Notes: Could not figure out how to use this server; could not find an example existing .net.za domain.

whois.nic.br.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^% (invalid syntax|invalid domain size|No match for domain "\S+")$

whois.nic.ch.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^we do not have an entry in our database matching your query\.$

whois.nic.io._Notes: I/O timeout.  Maybe use http://nic.io/cgi-bin/whois?query=rvm.io on the backend.

whois.nic.ir.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^% No entries found in the selected source\(s\)\.$

whois.nic.lk.NotExistRegexp: (?i)^this domain is not available in our whois database$
